solar-data-discovery/
├── frontend/ # React frontend app
├── backend/ # Python API proxy, caching, CSV handler
├── data/ # Sample data (e.g. benin-malanville.csv)
├── docs/ # Documentation and screenshots
├── README.md
├── requirements.txt # Backend dependencies
└── package.json # Frontend dependencies


---

## 📊 Sample Dataset

This project uses real-world solar data for demonstration purposes, including:

- **Benin (Malanville)** – File: `benin-malanville.csv`
- Sierra Leone
- Togo

These datasets include time series for solar irradiance and can be expanded to support custom uploads.

---

## ⚙️ Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/solar-data-discovery.git
cd solar-data-discovery
-- Backend
cd backend
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
